I"r<p>Use RTC memory, instead of EEPROM, in ESP8266 because it survives deep sleep mode to reduce power consumption even further</p>

<p>Write a simple number to RTC Memory, deep sleep it and then wake it up again to read the same number! Use the number of count, when to turn on the radio to process something.</p>

<p>Example of RTC Memory read</p>

<div class="language-c highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">bool</span>	<span class="n">system_rtc_mem_read</span>	<span class="p">(</span>
	<span class="n">uint32</span>	<span class="n">src_addr</span><span class="p">,</span>
	<span class="kt">void</span>	<span class="o">*</span>	<span class="n">des_addr</span><span class="p">,</span>
	<span class="n">uint32</span>	<span class="n">save_size</span>
<span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Example of  RTC Memory write</p>

<div class="language-c highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">bool</span>	<span class="n">system_rtc_mem_write</span>	<span class="p">(</span>
	<span class="n">uint32</span>	<span class="n">des_addr</span><span class="p">,</span>
	<span class="kt">void</span>	<span class="o">*</span>	<span class="n">src_addr</span><span class="p">,</span>
	<span class="n">uint32</span>	<span class="n">save_size</span>
<span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
